$timescale 1ns $end
$comment
  USB 2.0 Pro decoder error-detection fixture.
  Six packets:
    1. SETUP addr=0x12 ep=3                (clean)
    2. SETUP addr=0x12 ep=3                (BAD CRC5)
    3. DATA0 8 B DEADBEEF CAFEBABE         (clean)
    4. DATA0 8 B DEADBEEF CAFEBABE         (BAD CRC16)
    5. ACK                                 (clean)
    6. ACK                                 (BAD PID inverted-check)
  Each corrupted packet should appear red in the transaction
  table; the clean packets between them serve as visual controls.
  Regenerate via: dart run tool/generate_usb_error_fixture.dart
$end
$scope module tb $end
$var wire 1 ! DP $end
$var wire 1 " DM $end
$upscope $end
$enddefinitions $end
$dumpvars
0!
0"
$end
